Utilico Emerging Markets (LSE: UEM) is a large British investment company dedicated to investments in infrastructure, utility and related sectors in the emerging markets. Established in 2005, the company is a listed on the London Stock Exchange. The Chairman is John Rennocks.
Utilico Emerging Markets’ (UEM) investments focuses predominantly on the emerging markets of Asia, Latin America, Emerging Europe and Africa. UEM’s gross assets at 31 March 2017 was £579 million. UEM is managed by ICM Limited and ICM Investment Management Limited, which is authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority.
